      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so it's basically just a bunch of molecules reacting to heat? it seems almost like magic how the color and smell change so fast once it hits that temp. are there any other chemical reactions happening at the same time that affect the crust, or is it just the Maillard stuff?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
